      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes more sense. so if the steel is basically handling all the tension, does that mean there's anything happening deep inside the concrete itself besides just being crushed? like is there any interaction between the two materials at a molecular or structural level where they actually bond?",
      "source": "evaluator"
